ploads/2024/03/World-Happiness-Report.png?fit=750%2C774&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/World-Happiness-Report.png?fit=1090%2C1125&amp;ssl=1" /></a></p><p>自 2012 年以来每年发布的《世界幸福报告》<a href="https://worldhappiness.report/ed/2024/">刚刚下降到 2024 年</a>。今年他们关注的是年龄和幸福感。总体而言，美国在所有国家中<a href="https://worldhappiness.report/ed/2024/happiness-of-the-younger-the-older-and-those-in-between/">的排名</a>在17至29之间，但在年轻人方面表现较差。芬兰绝对位居榜首。</p><p>这些可视化是临床性的，考虑到报告的主题，这有点令人悲伤。应该有人整理数据并享受其中的乐趣。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/happiness/" rel="tag">幸福</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/rank/" rel="tag">排名</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 73663</post-id></item><item><title>观鸟和数据可视化</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/03/21/birding-and-data-visualization/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Thu, 21 Mar 2024 15:46:22 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Visualization]]></category><category><![CDATA[birds]]></category><category><![CDATA[Jer Thorp]]></category><category><![CDATA[learning]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=73655 </guid><description><![CDATA[Jer Thorp has combined birding and data visualization into a unique course called&#8230;<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/birds/" rel="tag">鸟类</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/jer-thorp/" rel="tag">杰·索普</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/learning/" rel="tag">学习</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> <a href="https://www.jerthorp.me/learning"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="73656" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2024/03/21/birding-and-data-visualization/binomials-binoculars/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/binomials-binoculars.webp?fit=782%2C684&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="782,684" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="binomials-binoculars" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/binomials-binoculars.webp?fit=750%2C656&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/binomials-binoculars.webp?fit=782%2C684&amp;ssl=1" src="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/binomials-binoculars.webp?resize=750%2C656&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="750" height="656" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-73656" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/binomials-binoculars.webp?resize=750%2C656&amp;ssl=1 750w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/binomials-binoculars.webp?resize=210%2C184&amp;ssl=1 210w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/binomials-binoculars.webp?resize=768%2C672&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/binomials-binoculars.webp?w=782&amp;ssl=1 782w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a></p><p> Jer Thorp 将观鸟和数据可视化结合到了一<a href="https://www.jerthorp.me/learning">门名为“双筒望远镜到二项式”的独特课程</a>中：</p><blockquote><p>我梦想从双筒望远镜到二项式作为一个混合学习网站。它适合有兴趣培养观察实践的编码员，以及想要深入了解其爱好产生的丰富数据池的观鸟者。</p><p>更广泛地说，它适合任何对自然、数据和创造力之间的重叠感兴趣的人。</p></blockquote><p>听起来不错。</p><p>学习如何可视化数据的最佳方法之一是将其应用到特定领域。您弄清楚数据背后的机制<em>和</em>上下文，这使得可视化变得有意义和有用。在这种情况下，您可以参与整个过程的所有部分。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/birds/" rel="tag">鸟类</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/jer-thorp/" rel="tag">杰·索普</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/learning/" rel="tag">学习</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 73655</post-id></item><item><title>通过生成人工智能形成国家身份刻板印象</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/03/20/national-identity-stereotypes-through-generative-ai/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Wed, 20 Mar 2024 07:33:14 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Statistics]]></category><category><![CDATA[AI]]></category><category><![CDATA[bias]]></category><category><![CDATA[midjourney]]></category><category><![CDATA[Rest of World]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=73645 </guid><description><![CDATA[<p> <a href="https://flowingdata.com/2024/03/20/national-identity-stereotypes-through-generative-ai/"><img width="750" height="471" src="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?fit=750%2C471&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?w=2410&amp;ssl=1 2410w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=750%2C471&amp;ssl=1 750w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=1090%2C685&amp;ssl=1 1090w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=210%2C132&amp;ssl=1 210w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=768%2C482&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=1536%2C965&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=2048%2C1287&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-