lass="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?w=2410&amp;ssl=1 2410w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=750%2C471&amp;ssl=1 750w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=1090%2C685&amp;ssl=1 1090w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=210%2C132&amp;ssl=1 210w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=768%2C482&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=1536%2C965&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=2048%2C1287&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?resize=400%2C250&amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?w=2180&amp;ssl=1 2180w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" data-attachment-id="73646" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2024/03/20/national-identity-stereotypes-through-generative-ai/bias-national-identity-midjourney/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?fit=2410%2C1514&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="2410,1514" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="bias national identity midjourney" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?fit=750%2C471&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/bias-national-identity-midjourney.png?fit=1090%2C685&amp;ssl=1" /></a></p><p>对于世界其他地区，Victoria Turk 打破了<a href="https://restofworld.org/2023/ai-image-stereotypes/">国家认同背景下</a>生成式人工智能的偏见。</p><blockquote><p>人工智能图像生成器中的偏差是一个很难解决的问题。毕竟，它们输出的一致性很大程度上取决于这些工具工作的基本方式。人工智能系统在接受训练的数据中寻找模式，通常会丢弃异常值，以产生更接近主导趋势的结果。它们的设计目的是模仿以前的情况，而不是创造多样性。</p><p> “这些模型是纯粹的联想机器，”普鲁蒂说。他举了一个足球的例子：人工智能系统可能会学会将足球与绿色场地联系起来，从而生成草地上足球的图像。</p></blockquote><p>在这种与刻板印象的趋同和谷歌双子座的强制多样性之间，有没有人尝试过将模型与人口统计数据结合起来，以找到一个介于两者之间的位置？</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/ai/" rel="tag">人工智能</a>、<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/bias/" rel="tag">偏见</a>、<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/midjourney/" rel="tag">中途</a>、<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/rest-of-world/" rel="tag">世界其他地区</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 73645</post-id></item><item><title> Flipbook实验，类似于电话游戏，但视觉效果</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/03/18/flilpbook-experiment-like-the-telephone-game-but-visual/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Tue, 19 Mar 2024 05:10:27 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Statistics]]></category><category><![CDATA[loss]]></category><category><![CDATA[Pudding]]></category><category><![CDATA[Russell Samora]]></category><category><![CDATA[sketch]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=73640 </guid><description><![CDATA[This looks fun. The Pudding is running an experiment that functions like a&#8230;<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/loss/" rel="tag">损失</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/pudding/" rel="tag">布丁</a>, <a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/russell-samora/" rel="tag">Russell Samora</a> ,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/sketch/" rel="tag">素描</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="four columns alpha"><a href="https://pudding.cool/projects/flipbook/">这看起来很有趣</a>。布丁正在进行一项实验，其功能类似于电话的视觉版本。在《电话》中，第一个人向他们的邻居低声传达一条消息，该消息会一直传递，直到您以完全不同的消息结束。你得到的不是消息，而是每个新人描绘的草图。</p><p>我在第 200 帧周围描画了一些东西，草图看起来已经像涂鸦了。我很好奇这一切到哪里结束。 </p></div><div class="five columns omega"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="73641" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2024/03/18/flilpbook-experiment-like-the-telephone-game-but-visual/flipbook-experiment/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/flipbook-experiment.png?fit=770%2C1298&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="770,1298" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="flipbook experiment" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/flipbook-experiment.png?fit=750%2C1264&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/flipbook-experiment.png?fit=770%2C1298&amp;ssl=1" src="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/flipbook-experiment-750x1264.png?resize=750%2C1264&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="750" height="1264" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-73641" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/flipbook-experiment.png?resize=750%2C1264&amp;ssl=1 750w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/upl